This paper deals with the problem of building trust in a network of online auctions by software agents, which involves understanding auction mechanisms and verifying desirable properties of a given mechanism. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational economics (cs.CE), as well as logic in computer science (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE) for the development of the semantic web services. Additionally, the use of abstract interpretation for translation and verification suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) for the underlying formalism and data structures.
